API Call Flow:

Frontend to rcmservice API:
The frontend calls the API to get the number of tasks/widgets for a user.
API:
GET https://iop-dev.nss.vzwnet.com:8080/rcmengine/switch/pathfinder/widget/banner/count?user_id=<user_id>
Response:
{"WIP": "3", "PAUSED": 0}

Backend (rcmservice) Calls switchService API:
The backend (in rcmservice) checks the user's role and calls the switchService API based on the role.

For SWITCH_MANAGER or CELL_SWITCH_MANAGER, it calls:
GET <switchService URL>/mgr/<user_id>
For SWITCH_TECHNICIAN, it calls:
GET <switchService URL>/tech/<user_id>
For TRANSLATION_MANAGER or TRANSLATION_ENGINEER, it calls:
GET <switchService URL>/trans/<user_id>
switchService Calls the Opstracker API:
Based on the environment, switchService makes a call to the Opstracker API.
In Production:
GET https://opstracker-api.eng.vzwcorp.com/c2/api/rest/getList.php
In Development:
GET http://txslpmtkpa4v.nss.vzwnet.com/c2/api/rest/getList.php
Response Back to Frontend:
The data from the Opstracker API is processed by switchService and sent back to the frontend for display.
